&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Opportunity&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;As a Senior/Staff Solutions Architect you will be the technical face of Interval for our largest&amp;nbsp;customers—designing, validating, and operationalizing modern data &amp;amp; AI architectures that span multicloud environments and leading SaaS platforms (Databricks, Snowflake, GCP, AWS, Salesforce,&amp;nbsp;and more). You’ll translate ambitious business outcomes into secure, performant, and governable solutions that unlock the power of Interval’s platform.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Architect end-to-end solutions that integrate Interval’s data-exchange, privacy, and AI&amp;nbsp;capabilities with customers’ existing cloud warehouses, lakehouses, and BI stacks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead technical discovery &amp;amp; design workshops with data, analytics, and ML teams;&amp;nbsp;produce reference architectures, sequence diagrams, and implementation plans.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prototype &amp;amp; run POCs showcasing secure LLM workflows, private-model training, and governed data-sharing on Interval’s EVM-backed network.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as a trusted advisor to enterprise stakeholders—CTOs, CDOs, and Heads of AI—on topics such as data-governance, compliance (HIPAA, GDPR), and ML-ops best practices.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate cross-functionally with Product, Engineering, and Sales to influence roadmap priorities and ensure customer success.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create reusable assets and enablement content that scale architectural best practices across the organization.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Evangelize Interval through conference talks, blog posts, and community contributions to the modern data stack and open-source AI tooling.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What We’re Looking For&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;8 + years designing and delivering enterprise SaaS or cloud data solutions, with recent&amp;nbsp;senior-level ownership of architecture or presales design.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deep hands-on expertise with at least one of Databricks, Snowflake, GCP, AWS or Salesforce Data Cloud.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working knowledge of machine-learning &amp;amp; LLM workflows (vector DBs, embedding pipelines,&amp;nbsp;fine-tuning, RLHF) and the surrounding ML-Ops toolchain.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Fluency in SQL and one scripting language (Python preferred); ability to read infrastructure-as-code&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong grasp of modern data-governance, security, and compliance patterns (encryption, IAM, row/column-level security).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exceptional written &amp;amp; verbal communication skills—you can whiteboard complex systems&amp;nbsp;and influence both executive and engineering audiences.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Nice to Have&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with blockchain-based data protocols, tokenization, or zero-knowledge proofs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prior success building reference architectures or contributing to OSS projects in the data/AI ecosystem.&lt;/li&gt;
